headline: Houston Teen Leads Effort to Close Texas's Digital Divide
summary: A Houston-area high school senior is helping bring technology and opportunity to students and communities that need it most. Rayaan Khan, a senior at Klein Collins High School in Spring, has taken a leading role in expanding 360Assist, the philanthropic arm of Works360, a global leader in technology enablement and demo-kit solutions. Texans can now nominate local organizations for future donation rounds at 360-assist.com/nominate .

headline: How the Story Around HP Is Evolving Amid Renewed Growth and Persistent Margin Risks
summary: HP's fair value estimate has inched upward, rising slightly to $28.28 per share from $27.97. Revenue growth projections have also been revised higher. This latest shift comes as Wall Street commentary reflects a cautiously optimistic outlook on HP's ability to maintain steady sales, particularly amid broader momentum in the IT hardware market driven by AI adoption. Stay tuned to discover how investors and followers can keep abreast of evolving expectations and market sentiment surrounding HP...
